    "updated_at": "2012-02-15T11:11:53Z",
    "body": "`str` currently seems to be used as a mixture of \"a string of characters\" and \"a vector of bytes\". The latter\n- exposes the string's implementation details\n- makes it possible to skrew up the internal string state.\n\nWhen you need access to a byte-vector, what is `str` giving that `vec` lacks?\n",
